This rename isn't consistent with `testBit_bit_succ` below
Should I do more renaming or no renaming? We have `Nat.zero_testBit` in the core now.
Matching core seems sensible, but perhaps you should do the renames separately to the refactor for visibility.
Presumably `| 1` is also faster than `+ 1`, if you're really micro-optimizing?
It's not faster in my tests. Also it would make proofs much more complicated.

This doesn't look like a good change to me. We have already settled on using `2 * n` and `2 * n + 1` in place of the old `bit0, bit1`, and these play better with ring theory tactics like `ring` and `linarith`. If you are doing this to improve the performance of the function, use a `@[csimp]` lemma instead. I don't see any reason to expect this to behave better in proofs.
It's very hard to review the diff if you move things here and redefine them at the same time. Could you split off a PR that first just collects these results into this file?
I need to move a bunch of `Nat.bodd` `Nat.div2` theorems if no definition changes at all. I tried to minimize the diff in #15567.

pullRequest.title: chore: redefine `Nat.div2` `Nat.bodd`
